<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,674,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
Lianescent shrub, branches glabrous except for the puberulous tips, internodes 
<quantity box="[1127,1243,786,812]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="3.0">3–23 mm</quantity>
. Stipules ca. 1 × 
<quantity box="[151,248,824,850]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate; petiole 
<quantity box="[497,602,824,850]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
, densely pubescent; blade 17–41 × 
<quantity box="[1044,1164,824,850]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="7.0">7–13 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate, oblong to elliptic, apex acute or less frequently obtuse or rounded, margin inconspicuously glandulose-serrate, base acute or less frequently rounded to cordate, adaxial face puberulous, abaxial sparsely puberulous and with black or amber-coloured resiniferous dots or striae, venation eucamptodromous, chartaceous. Flowers unisexual, yellowish, arranged in short 1–few-flowered axillary racemes, sometimes resembling fascicles; bracteoles ca. 
<quantity box="[317,410,1010,1036]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, narrowly lanceolate; pedicel 
<quantity box="[760,875,1010,1036]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="14.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="4.0">4–14 mm</quantity>
, densely pubescent; sepals subequal, ca. 2 × 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate, apex acuminate, margin entire, base truncate, densely pubescent; posterior petals 1.5–2.5 × ca. 
<quantity box="[195,269,1085,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, broadly oblong, apex rounded, glabrous; lateral petals 
<quantity box="[963,1064,1085,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
× 
<quantity box="[1100,1228,1085,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
, oblong, slightly constricted in the middle part, apex rounded, glabrous; anterior petal 
<quantity box="[993,1118,1122,1148]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="7.75" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.5">7.5–8 mm</quantity>
, spur 3.5–4 × ca. 
<quantity box="[1336,1431,1122,1148]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, slightly curved, blade 3.5–4 × 
<quantity box="[506,628,1160,1186]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4 mm</quantity>
, orbicular to subdeltoid, apex rounded to truncate, frequently slightly emarginate, asymmetric, glabrous; staminate flower: stamen filaments free or fused at the base, up to 
<quantity box="[1346,1435,1197,1223]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long, anthers up to 
<quantity box="[379,470,1234,1260]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long, connective appendages ca. 
<quantity box="[867,958,1234,1260]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long, whitish, apex truncate to rounded, frequently asymmetric, the two anterior stamens provided with filiform nectariferous appendages 
<quantity box="[1315,1436,1272,1298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous; pistillate flower: carpels 4, ovary ca. 1 × 
<quantity box="[826,898,1309,1335]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, glabrous, ovules 5–6/placenta, arranged in 2 longitudinal lines in each carpel, style ca. 
<quantity box="[642,732,1346,1372]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long. Fruit a loculicidal, membranaceous capsule, glabrous, each valve 25–36 × 16–20(24) mm, oblanceolate or elliptic, rarely obovate, apex emarginate, base long attenuate or acute. Seeds 7–9 × 
<quantity box="[534,633,1421,1447]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
including wing, obovate, base cuneate, glabrous, wing ca. 
<quantity box="[1345,1436,1421,1447]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide, margin toothed.
</paragraph>
